  "texts": [
    "Table III summarizes the main evaluation criteria, along with explanations and justifications for their inclusion.The criteria selected for this study, as summarized in Table III, provide a comprehensive framework for evaluating bias and fairness in LLMs.",
    "Quantitative metrics like accuracy, fairness scores, and bias amplification allow for objective comparisons across models, highlighting areas where biases may affect performance.",
    "In contrast, qualitative assessments, including expert reviews and ethical considerations, offer deeper insights into the subtleties of bias and fairness that are not easily captured by numerical metrics.",
    "Together, these criteria ensure a balanced and thorough evaluation, incorporating both the measurable aspects of model performance and the more subjective dimensions of ethical AI development.",
    "This approach recognizes the complexity of bias in AI and the necessity of addressing it through a multifaceted lens to develop more equitable and responsible technologies."
  ]
}